Read .ai/CONSTITUTION.md before making any code changes to this project.

This is the MIND project — a productized memory system for LLM agents.

Key rules:
- Layered architecture: Transport → App Services → Domain → Primitives → Kernel. Never import upward.
- All app services use AppRequest → AppResponse envelope pattern.
- New services must be registered in AppServiceRegistry (mind/app/registry.py).
- Type annotations required on all functions (mypy strict mode).
- Line length: 100 chars. Python 3.12+. Pydantic strict mode (extra="forbid", frozen=True).

Health check: After code changes, run `uv run python scripts/ai_health_check.py --report-for-ai`
then read `.ai/health/repair-prompt.md` for prioritized repair guidance.
- Follow .ai/CHANGE_PROTOCOL.md for what to update when changing code.
- Follow the rule routing table in .ai/CONSTITUTION.md §6 for module-specific rules.
